&lt;p&gt;Insourcing: Be part of the Solution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18 Week Support is the UK’s largest insourcing healthcare provider. We support NHS Trusts to help manage their patient pathways and to achieve their 18 week waiting time targets for the benefit of patients and their families. We provide a professional clinical team who work in conjunction with NHS own staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are actively seeking Dental Nurses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining 18 Week Support, you will be part of a highly successful organisation that is expanding rapidly. Working with 18 Week Support is unique,You will not be working in silo as it is normal with agency or locum staff, you will go into each Trust with an entire team of 18 Week support’s highly qualified professionals who work as a unit. This affords safety and security as a professional, allowing for safe and enjoyable working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a network of highly motivated, committed, and dedicated health professionals, working in several services nationally. In addition, you will have access to the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive rates of pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel and accommodation expenses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible work – as most of our work takes place at the weekend, you can fit it around your NHS commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have an excellent track record in delivering patient-focused care, please use the contact details below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: recruitment@18weeksupport.com or call 0203 966 9081&lt;/p&gt;
